One of the four Limpopo prison escapees has been rearrested. Abel Modiba (31), from Motjeteng village near Lenyenye outside Tzaneen, was re-arrested in Rwanda Village in the Nwamitwa area outside Tzaneen during a sting joint operation. Modiba and four others escaped when they jumped off from the back of a moving Police Van in Polokwane while being transported to Haenertsburg Police Station outside Tzaneen on November 14. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the manhunt for the three remaining escapees is still underway. One prisoner who was initially arrested for house robbery committed in Haenertsburg was re-arrested shortly after the escape. The remaining escapees were arrested for different crimes including house robberies and armed robberies which were also committed in Haenertsburg. The remaining escapees are identified as Thomas Nkuna (34) from Rwanda village in the Nwamitoa area outside Tzaneen and also staying in Wisani village in the Mhlaba-Cross area outside Tzaneen,Jeffrey Nkuna (27) from Rwanda village in the Nwamitoa area outside Tzaneen and George Nkuna (19) from Wisani village in the Mhlaba-Cross area outside Tzaneen. Ngoepe said the case of escaping from lawful custody was opened in this regard. The re-arrested suspect will appear before the Polokwane Magistrate Court soon for escaping from lawful custody. Anyone with information that can lead to theÂ  re-arrest of these three remaining escapees, may contact Colonel Linky Mathebula on 064 756 8218 or Detective Warrant Officer Andrew Ngamuni on 082 414 3031 or the crime stop number 0860010111 or the crime Line SMS 32211 or the nearest Police Station. 